<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-72-0053 </DOCNO><TEXT>The authors discuss the use of a plane mirror, attached to the elevatedstorage tank of a thermosiphon solar water heater, in order to lowerthe total profile of the system. The discussion includes a critical reviewof some of the simplifying assumptions that have been made by previousauthors who have proposed the use of mirror boosters in order to enhancethe energy collection of flat-plate receivers.</TEXT></DOC>